{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":6,"author":{"id":"173f4fceac25ce053a133bd829b18be7ad10b908"},"timestamp":1580916053,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlRWRpdDozNDgxOTcyMDA="},"target":"b8fb89fdd2ab1dddc3e5e5900b9990ae2076e1eaf851e87d47b26f96d71cfb41","message":"I recently [briefly described](https://github.com/leo-yuriev/t1ha/commit/605675b2fe6586e4608dc821fc71c4731d2c57d7) the \"blinding multiplication\" flaw of NH-approach hash functions. This seems to be an obvious thing, but many users do not know about it and have no idea about the possible consequences.\n\nThis looks to me to be a rather serious drawback, despite the low probability, since some of the data does not affect the hash value at all (e.g. _wyhash_ case).\n\nI think we need to come up with some kind of test that would allow us to clearly identify such flaws.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"173f4fceac25ce053a133bd829b18be7ad10b908"},"timestamp":1580916437,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU4MjQ2MTgwNg==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/99#issuecomment-582461806"},"message":"@wangyi-fudan, FYI.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"173f4fceac25ce053a133bd829b18be7ad10b908"},"timestamp":1580916744,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU4MjQ2NDM0MA==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/99#issuecomment-582464340"},"message":"@gzm55, FYI","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"a8f5cc6e3ca5c3c08a52bd4ccf655efd7b4bcadf"},"timestamp":1580950917,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU4MjY4NjQ0NQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/99#issuecomment-582686445"},"message":"Dear leo-yuriev:\nIt is not a significant problem in wyhash_v5.\nI write the porblem here: MUM(a,b)==0 when a=0 or b=0. so we have chance to loss entropy.\nwyhash_v5 use secret-mask-MUM: MUM(a^secret1,b^secret2)\nunless a==secret1 or b==secret2 we lose entropy.\nthe chance is as low as 2^-64.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"173f4fceac25ce053a133bd829b18be7ad10b908"},"timestamp":1580977744,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU4Mjc5MTIyMQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/99#issuecomment-582791221"},"message":"Dear @wangyi-fudan, as I commented https://github.com/wangyi-fudan/wyhash/issues/49:\n\nThe actual chance is _2^-63 per each multiplication_. Moreover, the later a zero rolls, (then) the greater the losses will be. For example, if a zero rolls at the end of the main loop, then the 1/4 of the data will be lost.\n\nFor many applications, this is an unacceptable flaw. Therefore, users should know about the price of speed, in order to make their own conclusions and assess the risks (regardless of how you assess the severity of the problem).\n\n---\n\nNow _SMHasher_ includes a table listing many drawbacks of hash functions, and many developers use this information to select hash functions. Therefore, it is irresponsible to keep silent about an aspect, especially if it is simple enough to explain it.\n\nIn addition, most (seem with single exception) hash function designers consider it unacceptable to intentionally leave a such known flaws (especially when ones are obviously).","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1581457565,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU4NDg2OTE4Mg==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/104#issuecomment-584869182"},"message":"Oh, I see. It only taking a few bits from len, not all. Thanks","files":null},{"type":5,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1581457583,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOkxhYmVsZWRFdmVudDMwMjgzNTA2OTQ="},"added":["bug"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1581530811,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU4NTMzODk2OA==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/104#issuecomment-585338968"},"message":"Note: Compare to https://github.com/blainsmith/libseahash/blob/master/src/seahash.c","files":null},{"type":4,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1581544696,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDExOkNsb3NlZEV2ZW50MzAzMjYxNTU2NA=="},"status":2}]}